# DARSHI TECH - Implementation Plan

DARSHI TECH is a modern, scalable, and secure educational and internship platform designed to connect students with internships, project catalogs, live classes, attendance tracking, and certificate generation. This document outlines the technical design, system architecture, database schema, security measures, and implementation steps.

## System Architecture

We will implement DARSHI TECH as a client-server web application in a monorepo structure:
- **`frontend/`**: Vite + React + Tailwind CSS + Lucide Icons + React Router. It will feature a collapsible left sidebar, responsive design, dark-mode/modern glassmorphism aesthetics, and clean dashboards.
- **`backend/`**: Node.js + Express.js + Prisma ORM + JWT + bcrypt. It will handle authentication, course catalogs, enrollment state, simulated payment validation, online class schedules, attendance, certificate generation with QR codes, and admin actions.
- **Database**: PostgreSQL (via Prisma). For quick local development and zero-configuration testing, we will configure Prisma to use SQLite by default but provide a direct toggle/instructions to use PostgreSQL.

